The initial slope is so high that it appears to be a vertical line. The literature recorded pressure in mbar, and even with units that small, the change in pressure is almost indistinguishable and the adsorption increases to almost saturation before the pressure noticeably changes. This could have been plotted incorrectly in NIST due to human error as the change in x for the first 7 points is almost, if not, indistinguishable to the human eye.
